SIMPLE: originally
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Originally
<hw>O*rig"i*nal*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>In the original time, or in an original manner; primarily; from the
beginning or origin; not by derivation, or imitation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God is <qex>originally</qex> holy in himself.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Pearson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>At first; at the origin; at the time of formation or
construction; <as>as, a book <ex>originally</ex> written by another
hand</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Originally</xex> a half length
[portrait].⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Walpole.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Originalness</ent>⟦br⟧
